in an enclosed truck, stopped before crossing

00:00:07.729 --> 00:00:09.630
an old, dangerous bridge.

00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:13.920
His avian cargo makes the truck too heavy
to safely cross.

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:16.200
So how could he make it lighter?

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:18.090
The birds.

00:00:18.090 --> 00:00:23.360
What if… he banged on the side of the truck,
scared the birds inside, and caused them to

00:00:23.360 --> 00:00:24.360
fly around?

00:00:24.360 --> 00:00:29.050
If they’re in the air they’ll weigh nothing
and he can safely cross the bridge!

00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:30.180
Right?

00:00:30.180 --> 00:00:34.980
Before we discuss those angry birds, I’d
like to thank Angry Birds 2 and Rovio Entertainment

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:37.620
for inspiring and sponsoring this video.

00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:43.039
It’s amazing how captivated we are by flinging
birds and tumbling tower physics.

00:00:43.039 --> 00:00:48.010
Millions of people alter their bird’s trajectory
to compensate for the kinetic energy of air

00:00:48.010 --> 00:00:53.539
blown by fans to perfectly knock out the block
holding up the precarious structure.

